The new cooperation treaty provides for the continuation of common types of assistance: girls’ and boys’ lyceums, French departments at universities, the French Institute, military, legal, medical and agricultural cooperation, support for the archaeological delegation.
Since 2009, the initiative "Getting Hearts and Souls" has been working, trying to reconcile the difficult task of aid and military activities, within which the service of "civilian-military steps" of the Ministry of Defense (Cimic), which was abolished in 2012, but achieved the succession of steps in the region due to the innumerable French organization.
These works, involving a large number of local workers, helped to mitigate the uprising: irrigation, wells, drinking water, forestry, fruit trees, protection of the soil and expansion of arable land.
What memory do we leave behind after <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>2 billion in military spending?
